System Context: We are performing a critical architecture upgrade on the client-side Fabric mod "am-ai mod" (package: com.itdragclick.client.ai) for Minecraft version 26.2.

Our goal is to resolve systemic issues with task abandonment, incorrect item name handling, broken chest placement, and vulnerable navigational pathing. We are integrating an advanced multi-task LIFO stack, real-time environment telemetry, a progressive crafting module, dynamic agricultural systems, and aggressive combat mechanics.

Please implement the following modules, command layers, state configurations, and logic patches across the codebase. Ensure all operations interacting with the physical world or input states run safely on the main Render/Game thread.

