### MODULE 1: DYNAMIC CHAT-BASED WHITELIST ENGINE
- Issue: The whitelist is static and hardcoded, making it impossible to add or remove friends at runtime.
- Fix: Create a runtime Whitelist Manager (AIWhitelistManager.java) backed by a local configuration file at config/am_ai_whitelist.json.
- Details:
  - Implement an immediate chat command intercept hook that completely bypasses the LLM processing pipeline:
    - "!AI whitelist add <player_name>": Instantly add the string to the whitelist file, reload the active memory cache, and announce in chat: "Added <player_name> to my protection whitelist!"
    - "!AI whitelist remove <player_name>": Remove the name from the file, update the active combat filter, and announce: "Removed <player_name> from my whitelist. Watch your back!"
  - Modify the active combat loop: Query this dynamic file per-tick. If a target entity matches an entry in the active whitelist array, the bot must completely abort attack operations.

